            {
                "s2_paper_id": "6ab50b5c9cf36dc250aeff99a17a10aa9616c483",
                "title": "Reproducible research in linguistics: A position statement on data citation and attribution in our field",
                "year": 2017,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 96,
                "reference_count": 23,
                "abstract": "Abstract This paper is a position statement on reproducible research in linguistics, including data citation and attribution, that represents the collective views of some 41 colleagues. Reproducibility can play a key role in increasing verification and accountability in linguistic research, and is a hallmark of social science research that is currently under-represented in our field. We believe that we need to take time as a discipline to clearly articulate our expectations for how linguistic data are managed, cited, and maintained for long-term access.",
